## 🎯 Key Updates Based on Your Feedback

### 1. Workflow Flexibility (MAJOR CHANGE)
- **Original**: Centralized workflow only; other modes in V1.0+
- **Updated**: 4 workflow modes now MVP features
  - Centralized: Admin drafts, all team leads approve, global publish
  - Ministry-First: Each team lead publishes independently
  - Hybrid: Admin template + leads customize + admin views conflicts
  - Self-Service: Volunteers self-signup, no approval
- **Why**: Your observation that "extending beyond centralized might feel too expensive" + different churches have different preferences
- **Impact**: Broader appeal, higher perceived value, clearer differentiation vs Planning Center

### 2. Pricing Restructured (MAJOR CHANGE)
- **Original**: Free $0/mo (limited), Starter $19/mo (100 vols, 5 min), Growth $49/mo (250 vols, 15 min), Pro $99/mo
- **Updated**: 
  - Free: Unlimited volunteers, 1 ministry (perfect for testing, worship-only teams)
  - Starter: 100 volunteers, 5 ministries, $19/mo
  - Growth: 250 volunteers, 15 ministries, $49/mo ← **Your church fits here**
  - Pro: 500 volunteers, unlimited ministries, $99/mo
  - Enterprise: Custom, multi-site, $199+/mo
- **Validation**: $49/mo for 250 vols / 15 min is reasonable; target >40% acceptance in interviews
- **Impact**: Free tier is now much more generous (great for small teams testing concept); your church validates Growth tier pricing

### 3. Calendar Feeds Promoted to MVP (MAJOR CHANGE)
- **Original**: Calendar feeds in V1.0+ (weeks 13+)
- **Updated**: Calendar feeds now MVP feature (weeks 1–12)
  - Personal: "My Schedule" (volunteer sees only their assignments)
  - Team: "Worship Team Schedule" (lead + team members)
  - Ministry: "Kids Ministry Schedule" (admin + leads only)
  - Privacy controls: public, password-protected, invite-only, private
  - iCal subscriptions: Auto-syncs to Google Calendar, Outlook, Apple Calendar
- **Why**: Your feedback "would be nice if platform could create calendar feeds"
- **Impact**: Volunteers get auto-syncing calendar (no manual imports), leadership gets cross-ministry visibility

### 4. Reminders Now Flexible (MAJOR CHANGE)
- **Original**: Email + SMS sent to all; user can opt-out globally
- **Updated**: User chooses per service type:
  - Email: Yes/No
  - SMS: Yes/No (opt-in, charges via Twilio overage)
  - Calendar invite: Yes/No
  - In-app push: Yes/No
  - None: Complete opt-out
  - Can configure per role (critical roles: SMS + email; regular: email only)
- **Why**: Your feedback "should be user decision to receive one of those, none of those, or both"
- **Impact**: Higher engagement (users opt-in to channels they prefer), fewer spam complaints, better open rates

### 5. Self-Contained Operation Made Primary (MAJOR CHANGE)
- **Original**: ChMS integration (Planning Center, Breeze, Rock) as primary path; CSV fallback
- **Updated**: Self-contained now primary:
  - Import options: CSV upload, manual entry, Google Sheets sync (future)
  - ChMS integration: Optional (Planning Center, Breeze, Rock OAuth)
  - No vendor lock-in: Export to CSV anytime
  - Export options: CSV, PDF, iCal feeds, push back to ChMS (optional)
- **Why**: Your feedback "would be good to be self-contained scheduling option, even if they don't want to push out to another ChMS"
- **Impact**: Faster onboarding (no OAuth setup required), lower barrier to entry, appeals to churches not using planning center

### 6. Interview Questions Updated (MAJOR CHANGE)
- **Original**: Questions focused on current pain, willingness to pay
- **Updated**: Questions now validate core value props:
  - Workflow preference: "Would you prefer centralized approval or independent ministry scheduling?"
  - Reminders: "Email reminders, SMS, both, or neither? What matters most?"
  - Calendar integration: "How important is iCal/Google Calendar subscription?"
  - Pricing: "For 50 vols / 15 min, what would you pay?" (test $49/mo)
  - Self-contained: "Do you prefer not to push back to Planning Center?"
- **Why**: These are your actual questions to ask beta churches
- **Impact**: Better validation of core differentiators before MVP build

