## 💡 Strategic Advantages of These Updates

### 1. Positioning
- **Old**: "Flexible scheduling for multi-ministry churches"
- **New**: "Flexible workflows, flexible reminders, flexible operation (standalone or ChMS-integrated). Works your way."
- **Advantage**: Much clearer differentiation vs Planning Center (which is rigid + expensive)

### 2. Pricing Perception
- **Old**: $19/mo for 100 vols felt limiting; $49/mo for Growth tier seemed expensive
- **New**: Free tier unlimited (perfect for testing); $49/mo for typical multi-ministry church feels fair
- **Advantage**: Better free-to-paid conversion; clearer value prop

### 3. Workflow Appeal
- **Old**: Centralized workflow only; not all churches would fit
- **New**: 4 modes; almost every church finds one that works
- **Advantage**: Broader TAM; higher likelihood of finding product-market fit

### 4. Technical Complexity
- **Old**: Could have added calendar feeds + flexible reminders + workflow modes in V1.0, creating longer MVP
- **New**: Integrated into MVP design from Day 1 (not retrofitted)
- **Advantage**: Cleaner architecture, no technical debt, faster to build

### 5. Customer Validation
- **Old**: Interview questions validated general pain points
- **New**: Interview questions validate specific value props (workflow, reminders, calendar feeds, self-contained)
- **Advantage**: Better confidence in MVP features before building; avoid building features no one wants

